AI agent that can orchestrate this entire workflow: Agent at Work | Deep Research UGC Ad Creation Master Agent Below is your end‑to‑end, click‑by‑click Tactical SOP to produce 30+ high‑converting, AI‑generated UGC ads for digital and info products in 2 hours, orchestrated by an agentic AI system with human oversight. It’s built for $10k/day profit targets at 95% margins, with strict QA gates and escalation triggers. Visual workflow overview AI UGC Ad Creation Flowchart (5 phases): Genspark AI CDN Preview of SOP hub (web) Agentic AI UGC Ad Creation SOP Hub: https://btidjlko.gensparkspace.com/ GensparkSpace 2‑Hour Agentic AI Production SOP — Timestamped, Click‑by‑Click, With Inputs/Outputs Notes: Owner: AI = Agent handles without human input; HO = Human oversight checkpoint; AI+HO = auto with human approve/reject. KPI Gates: If any gate fails, follow escalation triggers at the end of table. All folders are auto-created on kickoff with product_slug and timestamp. Table columns: Time | Phase | Owner | Click-by-Click Steps | Tools | Inputs | Outputs | KPI/QA Gates | Automation/Notes 0:00–0:05 | Phase 0: Kickoff | AI+HO | 1) Create project and folders: /brand/product_slug/yyyymmdd-HHMM/ 2) Initialize Google Sheet “Ad Research + Creative Tracker” with tabs: Competitors, Hooks, Scripts, Creatives, Launch Logs, KPI 3) Load brand/product brief, UVP, compliance constraints, banned topics (exclude right-wing politics) 4) Spin up task queue and timers | Google Drive, Google Sheets, Agent Orchestrator | Product brief, brand assets, banned topics list | Folder tree, tracker sheet, timers | Gate: Project init complete in <5 min | File naming: productslug_phase_step_vX.ext 0:05–0:15 | Phase 1: Research | AI | 1) AdNova: search by niche/keywords, filter by CTR/engagement, last 30–90 days; export top 50 2) SwipeKit.app: search ad angles/hook patterns; collect 30 exemplars 3) Shoptik Chrome Extension: pull UGC video references; download 10–20 reference files 4) Save all references + meta into Google Sheets | AdNova, SwipeKit.app, Shoptik, Google Sheets | Niche keywords, competitor list | 50–80 references with links, 10–20 files downloaded, populated sheet | Gate: ≥50 references, ≥10 video refs; Disqualify any political content | Enforce competitive score sorting: Hook Strength, Thumbstop Score, Social Proof 0:15–0:25 | Phase 1: Audience Blueprint | AI+HO | 1) Build audience persona blocks (problem-aware, solution-aware, product-aware) 2) Map FB/IG interests, behaviors, lookalikes (email list if available) 3) Draft 5 targeting packages: cold1–cold3, warm1, remarketing | Claude/ChatGPT, Google Sheets | Brand ICP, past buyers (if any) | Persona notes, 5 audience packages | Gate: Each audience has ≥5 interests and 2 creatives styles matched | Warm/remarketing uses exact event sources; HO verify brand fit 0:25–0:30 | Phase 1: Hook Bank | AI | 1) Generate 50 hooks across 8 angles: Problem agitation, Transformation, Before/After, Myth-busting, Proof-driven, Social Proof, Risk Reversal, Limited-time 2) Prioritize by thumbstop probability 3) Cluster to 10 primary hooks for production | Claude/ChatGPT | Research sheet, persona notes | 50 hook lines, top 10 shortlist | Gate: ≥10 hooks at ≥8.5/10 thumbstop score | Tag each hook with angle + persona stage 30:00–0:40 | Phase 2: Scripts | AI | 1) Generate 10 short UGC scripts (20–30s) and 5 mid scripts (35–45s) per top 10 hooks; include on-screen text, CTA, visual beats 2) Draft 5 testimonial variants, 5 demo variants 3) Draft 5 voiceover scripts | Claude/ChatGPT | Hook bank, persona map | 25+ scripts, 5 VOs | Gate: Script readability score < 7 grade; compliance ok | Compliance: no unverifiable claims; disclaimers where required 0:40–0:45 | Phase 2: Visual Character Plan | AI+HO | 1) Define 1–2 consistent characters (age, vibe, wardrobe) 2) Create character sheet for Ideogram Consistent Character 3) Draft 10 image prompt briefs | Ideogram (Consistent Character), imagepromolot.org | Brand styleboard, demo refs | Character spec, 10 image prompts | Gate: Character consistency >90% | HO approves character set 0:45–0:55 | Phase 2: Creative Generation (Stills) | AI | 1) Generate 20–30 stills with Ideogram (Consistent + Magic Fill) for hook thumbnails and ad cutaways 2) Enhance and upscale best 30 via Enhancor.ai 3) Background swap/product placement via SellerPic where needed | Ideogram, Enhancor.ai, SellerPic | Prompt briefs, product images | 30 final stills (4:5, 1:1, 9:16) | Gate: No artifacts; text legibility on mobile | Keep 3 aspect ratios for FB/IG placements 0:55–1:10 | Phase 3: Audio + VO | AI | 1) Convert 10–15 VO scripts in ElevenLabs (3 tones: friendly, authoritative, creator vibe) 2) Generate alt-language VO (if localized) 3) Save WAV/MP3 and transcript | ElevenLabs | VO scripts, tone guide | 10–15 VOs, transcripts | Gate: Voice clarity >95% ASR; pacing < 175 wpm | Label: hookID_tone_lang 1:10–1:25 | Phase 3: Video Assembly | AI | 1) Auto-assemble 30 ad versions via Arcads.ai templates: apply scripts, scenes, overlays 2) CapCut: quick manual tweaks, captions, emoji overlays, brand logo bug 3) Insert scroll-stopper first 2s; finish with CTA + URL | Arcads.ai, CapCut | Scripts, stills, VO, refs | 30+ ad videos (9:16, 1:1, 4:5) | Gate: Hook appears at 0–2s; CTA >26s; brand visible | Burn-in captions for silent autoplay 1:25–1:30 | Phase 3: QC Sprint | AI+HO | 1) Automated QA: aspect ratios, loudness -14 LUFS, length, typos, brand colors 2) Human speed pass: watch 10 random ads end-to-end 3) Flag fixes, auto-rerender | Internal QA bot, Human | 30 videos, 30 stills | QC pass list, rerender queue | Gate: ≥95% pass; <= 1 rerender per asset | Escalate if <95% pass rate 1:30–1:35 | Phase 4: Landing + Funnel | AI+HO | 1) Generate landing page in aifunnel.ai (headline, offer stack, guarantees, FAQs, schema) 2) Connect checkout on Shopify or GoHighLevel; ensure instant digital fulfillment 3) Generate 5-email sequence (welcome, proof, value, urgency, last-call) | aifunnel.ai, Shopify/GoHighLevel | Offer details, price, assets | Live landing page, connected checkout, email sequence | Gate: PageSpeed mobile >75; CVR est 8–15% | HO approves compliance and UX 1:35–1:40 | Phase 4: Tracking & UTMs | AI | 1) Create naming conventions: BRD-PROD-CRE-ANGLE-HOOKvX 2) Generate UTM templates for each creative 3) Publish event pixels (ViewContent, AddToCart, Purchase) | FB/IG Ads Manager, Shopify/GoHighLevel | Pixel IDs, domains | UTMs, pixel events live | Gate: Pixel fires verified; dedup ok | Use CAPI where possible 1:40–1:50 | Phase 4: Ad Setups | AI+HO | 1) Facebook/IG: Create campaigns: Creative Testing ABO (5 ad sets × 6 creatives), Warm (2×3), Remarketing (2×3) 2) Budgets: $20–$50/ad set/day for test 3) Placements: Advantage+ plus Reels; cap frequency warm | Facebook/IG Ads | Audience packs, 30 creatives | Drafted campaigns & ads | Gate: Policy check pass; URL working; pixel verified | HO sign-off then publish 1:50–1:55 | Parallel: Google Ads + SEO | AI | 1) SearchAtlas.com: generate keyword set, ad copy variants, RSAs 2) Build branded + competitor terms campaigns; add sitelinks 3) Create SEO snippets, FAQ schema, submit URL indexing | searchatlas.com, Google Ads, Search Console | Offer page URL, keywords | 2 search campaigns + SEO checklist done | Gate: QS est ≥ 7; CPC est within target | Low daily budget until FB/IG winners 1:50–1:55 | Outsourcer Brief | AI | 1) Auto-compose email to outsourcer with sample pack (top 5 creatives + brand kit + script pack) 2) Link to Drive folder and SOP hub 3) Request 10 variants in 24–48h | Gmail (draft), viralecomadz.com | Sample pack, instructions | Sent work order draft for HO | Gate: Files accessible; checklist attached | HO presses send 1:55–2:00 | Launch + Handoff | AI+HO | 1) Final publish FB/IG campaigns 2) QA live links, pixel events, preview creative 3) Set day-1 monitoring alerts and escalation rules | FB/IG Ads Manager, Alerts | All above | Campaigns live + alerting | Gate: Launch complete by T+120 | HO confirms go-live Quality gates and escalation triggers (hard rules) If any phase slips >15 minutes: auto-trim lower-impact tasks; escalate to HO. If asset QC pass <95%: auto-rerender and re-QC; if still <95%, escalate. If Ads policy check fails: auto-adjust copy (compliance profiles), retry; if 2nd failure, escalate. Performance post-launch: If cold CTR <2.5% or warm CTR <5% or CPA >$50 or CVR <8% by spend ≥$100/ad set, pause that creative and auto-rotate next-in-queue; escalate summary to HO. 30+ Creative variation plan (ensures coverage in one pass) Creative count logic: Hooks × Formats × Angles × Lengths × Characters Hooks: 10 Formats: 3 (Reels 9:16, Feed 1:1, 4:5) Angles: 3 (Proof/Testimonial, Demo, Risk Reversal/Guarantee) Lengths: 2 (20–30s, 35–45s) Characters: 1–2 Baseline combination: 10 × 3 × 3 × 2 × 1 = 180 possible. We cap first run at 30–40 by prioritizing top-impact: 10 hooks × 3 formats = 30; mix angles across the 30. Prompt library — Top 1% performers (copy/paste) Use these in Claude/ChatGPT. Replace bracketed fields before use. Hooks (50 variants generator) “Act as a DTC UGC strategist. Generate 50 thumb-stopping hooks for [PRODUCT] for [AUDIENCE], mapped to 8 angles (Problem, Transformation, Before/After, Myth-busting, Proof, Social Proof, Risk Reversal, Urgency). Format: Angle | Hook | Why it works (1 sentence). Score each 1–10 for Thumbstop Probability. Exclude politics.” UGC short scripts (20–30s) “Write 10 UGC scripts (20–30s) for [PRODUCT]. Structure: 0–2s hook on screen + VO, 3–8s pain agitation, 9–18s demo/proof, 19–26s offer/guarantee, 26–30s CTA. Include on-screen text, b-roll cues, emoji hints. Mobile-first. No medical/financial claims.” Testimonial scripts “Write 5 first-person testimonial scripts with specific, believable details for [PRODUCT], 25–35s each, social proof lines, and soft disclaimer.” Voiceover (3 tones) “Generate VO scripts for [HOOK_ID] in 3 tones: Friendly creator, Authoritative guide, Enthusiastic peer. Keep 140–160 words. Mark pauses and emphasis.” Ideogram consistent character “Create a consistent on-camera persona: [age][gender][vibe][wardrobe][background]. Style: natural daylight, phone camera realism, subtle branding. 9:16, 1:1, 4:5 variants. Add prop: [prop]. Maintain continuity across shots.” Image Magic Fill cutaways “Generate 10 product-in-context images for [SCENARIO], keeping the [brand color] accents, minimalistic background, high contrast for mobile. Include space for top/bottom text.” Caption overlays “Create 15 on-screen captions for [HOOK], max 6–8 words each, legible on 5.5” screens, high-contrast colors. Add emojis where appropriate.” Compliance fixer “Rewrite this ad copy to be compliant for Facebook/IG. Remove unsubstantiated claims, avoid targeting statements, no personal attributes. Keep persuasive tone. Return 3 variants.” SearchAtlas Google Ads copy “Produce 10 RSA headlines and 4 descriptions targeting [KEYWORD THEMES], include brand, benefit, and CTA variations. Output with pinning suggestions and path fields.” Email sequence (5 parts) “Write a 5-email sequence for [OFFER]. E1 welcome and fast win, E2 story + proof, E3 value drop, E4 urgency (ethical), E5 last chance. Each with preheader, preview text, and 1 CTA.” Outsourcer work order (viralecomadz.com) — ready-to-send template Subject: UGC Creative Pack — [Brand] [Product] — 10 Variants in 48h Hi Team, Attached is a sample pack with: Top 5 reference creatives (style cues) Brand kit (logo, colors, fonts) Scripts (10 short, 5 mid), VO files, overlays Character sheet and thumbnail stills Deliverables: 10 video variants (9:16, 1:1, 4:5), captions burned-in, CTA end cards, source files. Deadline: [Date+2]. Folder link: [Drive URL] Style notes: naturalistic UGC, strong hook in first 2 seconds, CTA at 26–30s. Compliance: no claims; no political content. Please confirm receipt and timeline. Thanks! Assembly and post-production details Arcads.ai template map: Hook bumper (0–2s) → Pain beat (3–8s) → Demo/Proof (9–18s) → Offer/Guarantee (19–25s) → CTA (26–30s) CapCut: Apply brand LUT, text animations, motion crop safe areas, auto-captions, music ducking, end slate. Naming conventions and UTMs Asset names: BRD_PROD_HOOK-ANG_FMT_LEN_v01.mp4 Campaign: BRD-PROD-CT-ABO-[DATE] Ad Set: AUD-[Cold1|Cold2|Warm|RMK]-INT-[TopInterest] UTMs: utm_source=facebook&utm_medium=cpc&utm_campaign={campaign_name}&utm_content={ad_name}&utm_term={interest} Launch structure and budgets (Day 1–2) Creative Testing ABO: 5 ad sets × 6 creatives, $20–$50/ad set/day Warm ABO: 2 ad sets × 3 creatives, $20/ad set/day Remarketing ABO: 2 ad sets × 3 creatives, $15/ad set/day Early kill rules (by $100 spend per ad set or 1,500 impressions): Pause if CTR<2.5% cold or <5% warm, CPA>$50, or CVR<8%. Rotate next creative from queue automatically. Tracking, dashboards, and alerts Sheet tabs: Ad Inventory, Live Ads, Metrics Raw, Daily Summary, Winner Board Metrics: Spend, Impressions, CPM, CTR, CPC, ATC rate, CVR, CPA, ROAS Alerts: Slack/email if CTR under threshold, CPA over target, pixel mismatch, spend anomalies >25% Compliance and brand safety checklist No personal attributes, health/financial claims, or politics (exclude right-wing political content) Disclosures as required, testimonials as experience-based opinions Copyright-cleared fonts, music, and footage Agent architecture (how the AI orchestrates) Modules: Research Harvester (AdNova, SwipeKit, Shoptik) → outputs scored reference bank Strategy Synthesizer → personas, audience packs, hook bank Script/Copy Factory (Claude/ChatGPT) → hooks, scripts, captions, emails Visual Engine (Ideogram, Magic Fill, SellerPic, Enhancor) → stills/thumbnails Audio VO (ElevenLabs) → VOs with tone variants Assembly Line (Arcads.ai, CapCut) → 30 ad videos QA & Compliance Bot → auto checks, HO gate Launch Manager (FB/IG + SearchAtlas/Google Ads) → campaign build, UTMs, pixels Outsource Coordinator (Gmail) → sends viralecomadz.com work order with sample kit Analyst & Auto-Scaler → day-1/2 performance rules and alerts Orchestration: Message bus + job queue with SLAs per phase; timers enforce 2‑hour cap; HO checkpoints at character approval, landing page approval, final publish. Knowledge base structure (created on project kickoff) /SOPs: this SOP, QA checklist, naming & UTMs /Research: AdNova, SwipeKit exports, Shoptik downloads /Scripts: hooks, scripts, VOs, captions /Assets: stills, thumbnails, videos, source files /Launch: campaign builds, screenshots, UTMs, pixels /Analytics: daily sheets, winner board, learnings Online SOP Hub: https://btidjlko.gensparkspace.com/ GensparkSpace Visual Workflow Image: https://cdn1.genspark.ai/user-upload-image/gpt_image_generated/30005596-634e-4ec5-b989-f0ec8ec26bb7 Genspark AI CDN What you’ll see at each checkpoint (inputs → outputs) Research: Inputs = keywords/competitors; Outputs = 50–80 references with scores Strategy: Inputs = references + ICP; Outputs = 5 audience packs + 10 hooks Scripts: Inputs = hooks; Outputs = 25+ scripts + 10–15 VOs Assets: Inputs = scripts + prompts; Outputs = 30 stills + 30 videos Launch: Inputs = creatives + UTMs; Outputs = live FB/IG campaigns, Google Search starter Human oversight points Approve consistent character and tone (0:40–0:45) Approve landing page and compliance (1:30–1:35) Final publish sign-off (1:55–2:00) Any escalation trigger events Performance targets (built-in gates) CTR cold ≥ 2.5%, warm ≥ 5% CPA ≤ $50 LP CVR 8–15% Maintain 95%+ margin on digital offers Would you like me to: Generate a complete set of visual flowcharts and infographics for each phase and embed them in your SOP hub? This will use AI image tools and may take additional time/credits. If yes, I’ll proceed and attach them to the hub using our available generation models. Draft and queue the outsourcer email in your Gmail with the sample kit attached for your one-click approval? Visual citations Workflow Flowchart: https://cdn1.genspark.ai/user-upload-image/gpt_image_generated/30005596-634